he has to be released into custody.

08:28.380 --> 08:31.122
We have been searching for Amber Foley
for weeks, Your Honor.

08:31.210 --> 08:34.623
-She's nowhere to be found.
-Keep looking. Until then, he's remanded.

08:35.800 --> 08:36.630
Bailiff?

08:40.140 --> 08:40.959
[door opens]

08:41.640 --> 08:43.631
Hang on, Justin. We're working on it.

08:44.100 --> 08:45.055
I know. Thank you.

08:45.390 --> 08:48.018
[Clay] We're still learning
all the ways we've been changed.

08:49.020 --> 08:50.476
All the things we've lost.

08:52.530 --> 08:54.066
I'm so fucking sorry.

08:57.490 --> 08:58.559
It's insane.

09:02.500 --> 09:06.209
But somehow I still feel stronger.

09:11.300 --> 09:12.119
[door closes]

09:13.760 --> 09:14.829
Wait, where's Justin?

09:15.470 --> 09:19.179
They'll only release him to a guardian,
and the judge won't move on it.

09:19.720 --> 09:22.632
We've filed emergency papers,
but it's a 24-hour minimum.

09:22.720 --> 09:24.927
I'll take the petition to Purdy.
He owes us.

09:25.020 --> 09:27.090
Do you wanna start on the order
for the school?

09:27.440 --> 09:28.259
Yeah.

09:28.650 --> 09:32.563
We're asking for a court order
to force the school to protect you.

09:33.320 --> 09:34.480
To keep him away from you.

09:35.190 --> 09:36.020
Thank you.

09:37.070 --> 09:40.403
Mom, is your firm...
I mean, are they cool with this?

09:40.490 --> 09:44.904
I've left the firm...
to work with Dennis on cases like this.

09:45.500 --> 09:46.319
Oh, that's...

09:48.580 --> 09:49.410
That's cool.

09:51.420 --> 09:52.705
[Bryce sighs]

09:55.130 --> 09:58.213
[Clay] We're just starting to figure out
how to go on with our lives.

10:08.480 --> 10:10.937
Coach said we could leave our lockers
till the end of the year.

10:11.020 --> 10:13.682
I'm transferring.
To Hillcrest.

10:14.110 --> 10:16.647
Hillcrest? You got the grades for that?

10:17.320 --> 10:18.389
Not exactly.

10:19.070 --> 10:21.652
Well, private schools
need fields, too, I guess.

10:23.530 --> 10:27.455
Yeah. And uniforms and all that shit.

10:28.910 --> 10:30.571
-[bag zips]
-Speaking of which...

10:33.090 --> 10:36.082
not all of my credits transferred,
so I'll be going in as a junior.

10:36.420 --> 10:38.547
Which means I'll see you
on the field this fall.

10:39.470 --> 10:42.962
-They're letting you play football?
-That's right. See you at the dance.

10:44.350 --> 10:45.169
Wait.

10:47.060 --> 10:50.018
So, you and Chloe?

10:50.770 --> 10:52.146
Yeah. Loyalty.

10:53.980 --> 10:55.106
It's a thing, huh?

10:57.740 --> 10:59.139
Take care of yourself, Zachy.

11:01.950 --> 11:05.022
[Clay] I say "go on" and not "move on"
because in some ways...

11:05.530 --> 11:07.998
we'll never completely move on
from what happened.

11:08.660 --> 11:11.242
Your meeting
with the district psychologist went well

11:11.580 --> 11:14.128
and the reports
from your diversion program are excellent.

11:14.210 --> 11:15.370
It was a good program.

11:16.050 --> 11:16.869
Tell me why.

11:18.010 --> 11:20.831
Um, well, at first, it was very difficult.

11:20.930 --> 11:23.080
You know, the long hikes and the camping.

11:23.680 --> 11:24.965
But after a few days,

11:25.720 --> 11:29.099
with everything else stripped away,
you're just left to your thoughts and...

11:30.520 --> 11:31.475
you learn things.

11:32.190 --> 11:33.225
And what did you learn?

11:33.810 --> 11:35.971
That I can choose how I respond to things.

11:36.570 --> 11:39.528
That even if I am feeling angry,
or lonely, or whatever,

11:39.610 --> 11:41.396
that I'm in control of my own actions.

11:42.070 --> 11:46.825
I can't control what other people do,
but I can control my response.

11:46.910 --> 11:50.789
Do you think you're ready to come back?
Do you think things will be different?

11:51.870 --> 11:52.780
Yeah, I think so.

11:54.210 --> 11:55.029
I'm ready.

11:58.210 --> 12:02.624
Principal Bolan is concerned
that we keep a very close eye on you.

12:03.840 --> 12:04.750
