13:12.290 --> 13:13.109
-Bye.
-Bye.

13:15.750 --> 13:16.569
What's up, man?

13:19.920 --> 13:21.831
[Clay] And I don't say
"get back to normal"

13:22.710 --> 13:24.587
because life will never be normal again.

13:27.180 --> 13:31.628
Before we start,
I am distrustful of religion.

13:32.470 --> 13:35.769
Okay. The service can be
whatever you want it to be.

13:35.850 --> 13:39.809
It's just... my mother always told us
we should abide,

13:40.860 --> 13:42.930
and have faith,
accept what's coming to us.

13:43.030 --> 13:45.942
And I think that teaches people
to be passive.

13:46.530 --> 13:49.693
I think abiding and acceptance
is bullshit.

13:50.530 --> 13:53.112
-Excuse my language.
-I don't disagree.

13:55.080 --> 13:55.990
So tell me,

13:56.370 --> 14:00.488
w-why choose a church
for Hannah's service?

14:01.040 --> 14:04.043
We, uh... we both come
from religious families,

14:04.130 --> 14:08.294
and it's something we drifted from a bit,
and thought maybe it was...

14:09.390 --> 14:12.712
something Hannah
perhaps should have had in her life.

14:12.810 --> 14:13.708
We were ashamed.

14:13.810 --> 14:14.629
[sighs]

14:16.350 --> 14:19.808
We were ashamed to have a funeral.

14:21.650 --> 14:22.639
Or a service.

14:23.320 --> 14:26.062
Butthen,
after everything that happened,

14:26.150 --> 14:28.607
if there is a God,
I want Him to see that...

14:31.700 --> 14:34.737
my little girl deserves His care.

14:37.080 --> 14:37.899
He will.

14:39.290 --> 14:40.200
He'll see that.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.245
[Mr. Baker] A few of the other places
we called,

14:45.090 --> 14:49.208
[sighs] given the circumstances
of Hannah's death...

14:51.720 --> 14:53.347
Let me assure you...

14:54.310 --> 14:56.016
there's no judgment from me.

14:57.310 --> 14:59.767
Not regarding Hannah's decision

15:00.810 --> 15:02.721
or the circumstances that led her there.

15:03.650 --> 15:08.064
And I hope one day
you'll release yourselves

15:08.150 --> 15:12.655
from any shame
you might still be feeling as well.

15:24.460 --> 15:28.453
[Clay] Life is divided into "Hannah"
and "after Hannah."

15:29.340 --> 15:31.171
[Clay] I don't have anything
to compare it to.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.131
I've lived here all my life.

15:34.850 --> 15:37.637
It's like asking Han Solo, "How is space?"

15:38.970 --> 15:41.552
Wow. You're an actual nerd, aren't you?

15:42.440 --> 15:44.601
