16:47.290 --> 16:49.087
[Clay] But we hold on to the memories...

16:52.260 --> 16:54.046
[tattoo machine buzzing]

16:54.130 --> 16:55.677
...because they're what we have left.

17:03.230 --> 17:04.549
You're doing great this time.

17:10.610 --> 17:12.771
You can look now.
No more comma.

17:21.160 --> 17:21.979
Thank you.

17:22.080 --> 17:23.616
[Clay] And we have an urge
to remember,

17:24.750 --> 17:26.206
to commemorate another time,

17:27.750 --> 17:29.490
to hold on to this as long as we can.

17:31.710 --> 17:33.166
The thing I'm most afraid of...

17:36.880 --> 17:37.835
