- Hello, welcome home

18:29.770 --> 18:31.010
[Clay] But today...

18:33.070 --> 18:34.310
we begin to let go.

18:59.590 --> 19:02.639
We're here to say goodbye to Hannah.

19:05.390 --> 19:08.598
One act does not define a life.

19:09.810 --> 19:12.768
We celebrate the richness of her life,

19:12.940 --> 19:16.979
even as the tragic circumstances
of her death cannot be forgotten.

19:19.820 --> 19:23.654
[Andy] It does my heart good to see
so many of Hannah's friends here today.

19:25.240 --> 19:27.037
Hannah had the biggest heart,

19:27.790 --> 19:30.247
which she so generously shared
with all of us.

19:31.750 --> 19:34.662
So, please, be kind to each other.

19:37.420 --> 19:41.174
She dreamed of going to New York
to become a writer.

19:43.390 --> 19:48.134
I'm not sure when that dream
began to feel imp055ible to her.

19:50.020 --> 19:53.433
Hannah was my dream.

19:56.270 --> 20:01.560
And now I get to dream for Hannah
as well as for myself.

20:01.650 --> 20:03.277
And so do all of you.

20:04.740 --> 20:05.900
So, please,

20:07.240 --> 20:09.572
dream your dreams.

20:10.080 --> 20:11.707
And dream them for Hannah,

20:12.290 --> 20:14.918
and don't let anyone
take them away from you.

20:16.840 --> 20:17.989
Don't ever let them go.

20:23.300 --> 20:26.383
Hannah Baker came into my life
at the end of one summer

20:26.470 --> 20:29.507
like a star that fell to Earth.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.766
Like nothing I had seen,

20:34.190 --> 20:35.430
like no one I had ever met.

20:36.980 --> 20:40.359
She was funny, and smart,

20:41.900 --> 20:45.154
and moody, and... and maddening,

20:45.990 --> 20:47.696
and beautiful.

21:06.550 --> 21:07.380
And...

21:11.680 --> 21:12.556
I loved her.

21:15.100 --> 21:16.476
I loved her so much.

21:19.690 --> 21:22.727
And I ask her every day
why she did what she did.

21:24.950 --> 21:26.235
But I get no answers.

21:30.330 --> 21:32.036
She took those with her when she went.

21:33.290 --> 21:35.497
Leaving me, all of us,

21:36.670 --> 21:41.369
angry, empty, confused.

21:45.130 --> 21:47.041
And I know that hurt won't ever go away.

21:49.300 --> 21:51.632
But there will come a day
when I don't feel it every minute.

21:52.470 --> 21:56.349
And the anger won't be so hot,
and the other feelings will fade,

21:59.600 --> 22:01.181
and I'll be left with only love.

22:06.610 --> 22:08.237
A good friend once said to me,

22:09.610 --> 22:11.737
"I can love you and still let you go."

22:17.040 --> 22:18.075
So, Hannah,

22:21.710 --> 22:22.529
I love you,

22:25.260 --> 22:26.204
and I let you go.

22:30.140 --> 22:31.038
And I miss you.

22:35.270 --> 22:36.919
And I hope that wherever you go next,

22:38.770 --> 22:39.759
you feel peace,

22:41.650 --> 22:42.765
you feel safe

22:44.730 --> 22:46.436
in a way that you never did here.

22:56.290 --> 22:57.405
Wherever you go next,

22:59.790 --> 23:01.246
I hope you know that I love you.

23:40.460 --> 23:43.452
[people sniffling, coughing]

23:44.130 --> 23:46.121
[bell tolling]

23:49.170 --> 23:52.003
[chatter]

24:01.390 --> 24:02.345
Everything okay?

24:05.110 --> 24:07.066
Yeah. No, Ijust, um...

24:08.440 --> 24:10.772
-I was just taking a minute.
-Of course.

24:11.820 --> 24:12.775
I'll leave you to it.

24:14.200 --> 24:15.189
Can I ask you...

24:20.500 --> 24:22.400
do you believe in the immortal soul?

24:23.960 --> 24:24.779
I do.

24:25.710 --> 24:27.587
And do you think Hannah is going to hell

24:29.000 --> 24:30.251
because she killed herself?

24:35.640 --> 24:36.459
I don't.

24:37.180 --> 24:40.843
I think the God I believe in, a just God,

24:41.770 --> 24:44.386
would have mercy on a soul like hers.

24:46.730 --> 24:50.359
And if God forgives her, we should.

24:51.530 --> 24:55.523
I believe we should follow
His example, sure, but...

24:57.280 --> 24:58.520
it's not always easy.

25:01.830 --> 25:02.785
And do you think...

25:05.670 --> 25:07.319
Does God forgive us?

25:09.420 --> 25:10.660
The people who let her down?

25:12.210 --> 25:13.120
I think He does.

25:17.050 --> 25:22.090
Clay, you don't have to believe
in the immortal soul

25:22.810 --> 25:25.722
to believe that people live on with us.

25:26.600 --> 25:27.840
Wait, what do you mean?

25:28.980 --> 25:31.778
Just that... we've lost Hannah,

25:32.940 --> 25:34.942
but not the things she gave us.

25:36.150 --> 25:40.860
Compassion, understanding, love.

25:43.040 --> 25:44.029
Those don't go away.

25:47.500 --> 25:49.491
